01:36:19.098 --> 01:36:23.331
So I was wondering, if you do
exams or homework problems

01:36:23.331 --> 01:36:25.904
throughout the semester, you
can, maybe, also better

01:36:25.904 --> 01:36:30.350
monitor how the students develop
compared to having one

01:36:30.350 --> 01:36:32.326
big exam on the end.

01:36:32.326 --> 01:36:34.796
And then maybe using [INAUDIBLE]
lectures.

01:36:34.796 --> 01:36:38.860
PROFESSOR: Right, so having
continuous assessment is one

01:36:38.860 --> 01:36:39.500
phrase for it.

01:36:39.500 --> 01:36:42.170
It allows you to monitor, make
sure things are going OK.

01:36:42.170 --> 01:36:44.640
So all of a sudden you don't
find, oh my god, the person

01:36:44.640 --> 01:36:45.100
didn't know anything.

01:36:45.100 --> 01:36:47.220
They got a third, which is
like straight D's in your

01:36:47.220 --> 01:36:48.770
whole undergraduate.

01:36:48.770 --> 01:36:51.140
So in Oxford and Cambridge
things are graded on first,

01:36:51.140 --> 01:36:52.000
second, third.

01:36:52.000 --> 01:36:54.980
And all of a sudden you had had
no idea the student was

01:36:54.980 --> 01:36:56.600
going to get a third,
or they were sick or

01:36:56.600 --> 01:36:57.660
something like that.

01:36:57.660 --> 01:36:59.340
So I think, yeah.

01:36:59.340 --> 01:37:04.100
So homework problems and exams
have a really good purpose in

01:37:04.100 --> 01:37:06.890
assessment and helping students
get feedback on how

01:37:06.890 --> 01:37:09.620
they're doing as well.

01:37:09.620 --> 01:37:12.140
So for that purpose,
grading is useful.

01:37:12.140 --> 01:37:16.300
And one solution to that
dilemma-- because I don't like

01:37:16.300 --> 01:37:18.940
to grade exactly because
it stresses them

01:37:18.940 --> 01:37:19.790
out with the grade--

01:37:19.790 --> 01:37:22.030
is to give them the solution
set right away.

01:37:22.030 --> 01:37:24.580
So they can get feedback from
the solution set whether they

01:37:24.580 --> 01:37:28.103
understood things, not whether
they had a 90 or and 80, but

01:37:28.103 --> 01:37:29.620
whether it made sense to them.

01:37:29.620 --> 01:37:31.980
And that's, I think, a much
more important thing.

01:37:31.980 --> 01:37:34.160
But then the other part of
grading, which is that it's

01:37:34.160 --> 01:37:35.310
used publicly--

01:37:35.310 --> 01:37:37.630
as part of your record and
written to other people--

01:37:37.630 --> 01:37:40.420
that part of grading I
think is not right.

01:37:40.420 --> 01:37:43.440
I don't think it's morally right
to, basically, reveal

01:37:43.440 --> 01:37:45.860
information about students to
other people without their

01:37:45.860 --> 01:37:46.300
permission.

01:37:46.300 --> 01:37:48.530
I don't think that should be the
purpose of the university.

01:37:48.530 --> 01:37:51.600
But the other purpose of
grading, helping students know

01:37:51.600 --> 01:37:52.550
where they are.

01:37:52.550 --> 01:37:54.980
And helping us know where they
are so we can help them more,

01:37:54.980 --> 01:37:56.550
I think, is a completely
valid purpose.

