01:38:43.780 --> 01:38:45.210
So you want them to do that.

01:38:45.210 --> 01:38:46.930
And you can do that in
class and homework.

01:38:46.930 --> 01:38:49.900
And the take-home exams that
we had when I was an

01:38:49.900 --> 01:38:51.405
undergraduate had that
purpose too.

01:38:51.405 --> 01:38:54.510
You spent 24 hours really
learning stuff.

01:38:54.510 --> 01:38:57.170
So that purpose is
very valid too.

01:38:57.170 --> 01:38:59.740
But it's also very valid to know
where the students are.

01:38:59.740 --> 01:39:03.230
So for example, that basically
closes the feedback loop.

01:39:03.230 --> 01:39:05.090
You're doing all this stuff.

01:39:05.090 --> 01:39:07.000
And now you're seeing
the result of it.

01:39:07.000 --> 01:39:08.990
And you want to know, well,
did any of it take?

01:39:08.990 --> 01:39:10.160
Did any of it stick?

01:39:10.160 --> 01:39:12.920
And if none of it did, well,
maybe you want to change what

01:39:12.920 --> 01:39:13.350
you're doing.

01:39:13.350 --> 01:39:16.654
AUDIENCE: Oh, but you
cannot evaluate a

01:39:16.654 --> 01:39:17.598
person every week, right?

01:39:17.598 --> 01:39:21.106
And that's what drives students
to copy solutions

01:39:21.106 --> 01:39:25.360
because they care
about the grade.

01:39:25.360 --> 01:39:26.922
[INAUDIBLE].

01:39:26.922 --> 01:39:28.110
PROFESSOR: That's
why distinguish

01:39:28.110 --> 01:39:29.930
two senses of evaluate.

01:39:29.930 --> 01:39:31.260
There's evaluate
for the purpose

01:39:31.260 --> 01:39:32.590
of helping the students.

01:39:32.590 --> 01:39:34.570
And there's evaluate for the
purpose of publishing their

01:39:34.570 --> 01:39:36.900
grades elsewhere.

01:39:36.900 --> 01:39:38.920
And it's the publishing
their grades elsewhere

01:39:38.920 --> 01:39:40.050
that worries them.

01:39:40.050 --> 01:39:41.840
So you want to minimize
that part.

01:39:41.840 --> 01:39:44.620
And you want to do as much
evaluation towards helping

01:39:44.620 --> 01:39:45.620
them as possible.

01:39:45.620 --> 01:39:48.140
So a solution set-- for example,
one thing you can do

01:39:48.140 --> 01:39:49.450
is say OK, here's the
solution set.

01:39:49.450 --> 01:39:52.170
Ask me about anything
that's confusing.

01:39:52.170 --> 01:39:54.430
And then you can put some of
the responsibility for this

01:39:54.430 --> 01:39:56.780
evaluation onto them so
it's self evaluation.

01:39:56.780 --> 01:39:59.830
But you're still using the
homework for evaluation.

01:39:59.830 --> 01:40:01.630
It's just you're not
trying to say look,

01:40:01.630 --> 01:40:02.290
that's the main thing.

01:40:02.290 --> 01:40:04.370
I'm going to use that to tell
everyone else about it.

01:40:04.370 --> 01:40:06.050
That's what worries them
and produces copying.

01:40:06.050 --> 01:40:08.580
So you want to minimize that
as much as possible.

